This paper deals with stochastic finite automata, which are commonly used in language and speech processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses efficient sampling algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with graph algorithms and strongly connected components, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SD (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with probability distributions and random strings, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
